
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-carrel-ipsecme-controller-ike-01.txt'>
    <title>"IPsec Key Exchange using a Controller", David Carrel, Brian Weis</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-carrel-ipsecme-controller-ike-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document presents a key exchange method allowing devices managed by a controller (e.g., an SDN management station) to create private pair-wise IPsec SAs without IKEv2 or any other direct peer-to-peer session establishment messages.  The method can be used when a full mesh of IKEv2 sessions between IPsec devices is not appropriate.</description>
    <dc:date>2019-03-10T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
